the togo sofa now vs then 🧸🤎 this story of this sofa will always be my favorite- it was a wedding gift to my parents & when I was little I would sneak into my parents room every night to sleep on this exact sofa. It was my comfy zone.

Years passed, my dad moved, & the sofa got lost. I was fixated on it & constantly told to let it go… but i am not one to let things go ever. I did some digging & managed to locate the sofa AND ottoman in a storage unit in Texas.

I had it shipped to California and now the togo sofa is back where she belongs… & I even have the cow blanket too 🥹 the end!

not done w/ Cabo content just yet 🧉as per request, here are some of my Cabo recs: 

♡ Vice Roy Los Cabo- best hotel in Cabo imo. Vibes are immaculate, food & drinks 10/10, everyone is so nice, & the will make you cry. 

♡ Bagatelle- the food was SO GOOD. Get the guac. We went at the wrong time & it was empty, but Sunday brunch or a later dinner looks so fun if ya like dancing on tables to abba ◡̈ 

♡ Acre: for a farm to table vibe, Acre is it. We went for dinner, but really want to do a brunch here next time. I would actually recommend over flora farms. 

♡ Sage: the cutest & yummiest little restaurant in San Jose Del Cabo. Very aesthetic and food + cocktails were amazing. Homemade pasta daily 🤌🏼

♡ Rubas bakery: the food highlight of our trip this year was this little bakery in town!! The lox & bagel was homemade and so good.

♡ Las Lupita’s: best tacos you’ll ever have. The end. 

♡ Edith’s: we skipped Edith’s this trip but it’s always a good time and to date the best Caesar salad I’ve ever had. 

Feel free to add ur recs for those planning a trip to cabo ☀️

#cabosanlucas #sanjosedelcabo #viceroyloscabos

a list of things in my Copenhagen AirBNB that just make sense 🦢🌷🗝️💫

- colorful walls + fun color combos. The pink & yellow took me outtt. No boring beige vibes.
- the curtains, the colors, the fabric. 10/10
- so many fun mismatched lamps & funky chairs.
- instead of one large duvet on, they do two twins. It is a game changer. 
- chiffon “tubes” of fabric in pretty colors to hide ugly cords- like a  scrunchie cord cover. 
- a deep couch. I now NEED a deep couch.
- the kitchen faucet dispenses delicious ice cold water, hot water for tea, AND ice cold sparkling water. All in one. 
- never thought I’d see the day but loving the pops of wood!!! So cozy. 
- the crown moulding. It’s so good in every room & all I have ever wanted 

#danishdecor #copenhagen #airbnbfinds #decorporn
